d what became the Bodleian Library at Oxford. In modern times, probably the most famous bearer has been the film star  Humphrey Bogart  (  1899–1957 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":5,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Humphrey Bulkeley Esq. was born in 1450, in Woore, Shropshire, England, his father, Hugh de Bulkleley, was 31 and his mother, Helen Wilbraham, was 36. He married Cecily Moulton in 1484, in Shipton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1535, in his hometown, at the age of 85."},"et":{"1450–1535":"1450–1535","1440–Female":"1440–Surnud","1452–1518":"1452–1518","1450–1559":"1450–1559","1486–Male":"1486–Surnud","1489–1571":"1489–1571","1420–1490":"1420–1490","1415–1470":"1415–1470","about 1470":"umbes 1470","1484":"1484","1440":"1440","1450":"1450","1571":"1571","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","1415":"1415","1535":"1535","1489":"1489","1455":"1455","Abt 1486":"umbes 1486","1420":"1420","1486":"1486","1452":"1452","1518":"1518","1559":"1559","Woore, Shropshire, England":"Woore, Shropshire, England","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Shipton, Church-Stretton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Shipton, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Woodley, Cheshire, England":"Woodley, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"1450–1535":"1450–1535","1440–Female":"1440–Kuollut","1452–1518":"1452–1518","1450–1559":"1450–1559","1486–Male":"1486–Kuollut","1489–1571":"1489–1571","1420–1490":"1420–1490","1415–1470":"1415–1470","